title: Market share of selected TV stations in Germany 2019
summary: This grouped bar chart shows Audience market share on the Y-axis for 8 different TV Channels for 2 groups Total audience (3 years and older), and 14-49 years that are presented on the X-axis.

TV Channel ZDF had the maximum Audience market share among all 2 groups, and it was for Total audience (3 years and older). The minimum Audience market share was observed in TV Channel kabel eins for 14-49 years.
In TV Channel RTL, 14-49 years had the highest Audience market share among all 8 TV Channels and it has the lowest Audience market share in TV Channel kabel eins.
There is a gap of 114.0 between the highest and lowest Audience market share found for 14-49 years in TV Channel RTL and kabel eins.

max_summary: This grouped bar chart represents 8 different TV Channels on X-axis for 2 groups Total audience (3 years and older), and 14-49 years. On the Y-axis it shows their corresponding Audience market share.
In TV Channel ZDF, Total audience (3 years and older) had the highest Audience market share 127.0 among the 2 groups and in kabel eins, 14-49 years had the lowest Audience market share 5.0.
In TV Channel RTL, 14-49 years had the highest Audience market share among all 8 TV Channels and it has the lowest Audience market share in TV Channel kabel eins.
TV Channel RTL and kabel eins had the biggest gap of 114.0 between the highest and lowest Audience market share found for 14-49 years.
Among all 2 groups, Total audience (3 years and older) had the gap of 98.0 between the maximum and minimum Audience market share observed in TV Channel ZDF and RTL II respectively.
Averaging all 2 groups Total audience (3 years and older), and 14-49 years, the TV Channel RTL is the maximum Audience market share and RTL II is the minimum Audience market share.
